I AM YOU is a must-watch #film streaming on Amazon and Apple iTunes now! My friend @SoniaNasseryCole is an award-winning Afghan American filmmaker, and the Director and Producer of this profound and deeply moving film. 

There are over 70 million refugees in the world, and half of these are children. It is a life filled with hardship, struggles and uncertainty beyond belief. Sonia’s film, I AM YOU, takes you through the life of three Refugees who leave everything behind and make their way to safety while encountering obstacles that shape their character and their destiny.  

“I Am You is inspired by the story of a refugee, the horrendous conditions before his heroic journey, the heartbreaking indifference confronting him along the way, and the uplifting power and humanity found in hope, truth and justice.” 

Please take a moment to check out I AM YOU on Amazon or iTunes. Once you watch the film, please consider taking a moment to leave a rating of the film and review of your thoughts — this last step will help in Sonia’s mission of spreading knowledge and amplifying voices of those who need to be heard. The more attention we can bring to this cause the more lives we can change together. 🙏🏻❤️ 

🎥 Go to @IAMYOU.film and check out the link in their bio to watch the film.

node.text:
Do you want to know the FASTEST way to END SUFFERING?  

It’s actually very simple... 

Trade your expectations for appreciation and your WHOLE WORLD will change in an instant. 

I truly believe that we’re living in the greatest time in HISTORY — creativity, innovation, and opportunity exist like never before. We’re blessed to live in an abundant time, where so many of our desires are met instantly — at the touch of a button, the click of your mouse, the swipe of your thumb. Social media links us to people all over the world — we can count the number of “friends,” and we get a dopamine boost with every 👍🏻, ❤️, or 😂.

The crazy thing is, that most of us believe that kind of instant gratification = happiness. But what we’re really experiencing when we’re focused on what we GET in life is the ILLUSION of happiness and fulfillment. We live in a culture of EXPECTATION where we are focused on ourselves and our own needs. And when our desires and expectations aren’t met IMMEDIATELY, we feel lack, loss, frustration, rejection…all states of suffering.  

But the TRUTH is, what makes us TRULY happy in life is NOT what we GET, it’s what we GIVE. After all, the secret to living, is giving! 

When we make the choice to focus on appreciation, growth, contribution, and LOVE, we’re making the conscious decision to live in a beautiful state — no matter what.  🙏🏻❤️

Right now, think of something or someone that you’re grateful for and that you can appreciate in THIS moment. Let’s hear from you in the comments — what do you APPRECIATE today?

node.title: The Fastest Way to End Suffering

👥 20,000 Households 
🌍 129 Countries  
💬 7 languages translated simultaneously!  

Here’s a peek inside the room at this past weekend’s Unleash the Power Within Virtual event.  

This event was particularly meaningful as it marked our sixth UPW Virtual in a year! That’s right, our very first UPW in HISTORY came to life last July, and since then we’ve been able to connect with over 1.1 MILLION humans virtually — partners, parents, kids, friends, co-workers, peer groups...and even their four-legged friends! 👨‍👩‍👧‍👦 👶👨🏼👩🏾🐶🐈🐠 It’s such an honor to be invited into your kitchens, living rooms, home offices, backyards... and even along for the ride in some of your traveling boat ⛵and van 🚙 adventures! This last year has certainly been unique, and it is such a beautiful and unforgettable experience to connect with you all in such an intimate way.  

The most powerful story is the COMEBACK STORY — where we rise from the ashes and rebuild a life that is truly extraordinary 🔥. A life of MEANING and ULTIMATE FULFILLMENT...on OUR terms. I’m so proud of every single person in the room this past week for showing up, doing the work, and playing full out! 🙌 💥 I can’t wait to see how you will use the tools and strategies to create more joy, more happiness, more LOVE in your lives.

Were you with us this past week, or at any of our Virtual UPWs this year? Drop a comment and let us know — what was one of your biggest takeaways?  

‼️ We also shared something truly exciting — after two full years, our Unleash the Power Within event in November will be ⚡LIVE IN PERSON!⚡ Click the link in my bio for details — I look forward to seeing and serving many of you there!!

Traumatic Brain Injury impacts 2 MILLION people every year.  

Quiet Explosions: Healing the Brain, is a powerful documentary by my friend, Emmy Award winning filmmaker Jerri Sher, that shows us how veterans and athletes who have suffered from TBI and PTSD can fully recover — it’s truly miraculous!  

Here’s a heartbreaking statistic — on average, we lose 22 veterans a day to suicide. Post-Traumatic Stress Disorder is truly an invisible illness, one that countless American heroes suffer from in silence.  

To honor #ArmedForcesWeek, Quiet Explosions is available to stream from now until May 28th — tickets include both the full-length documentary, as well as a riveting conversation between filmmaker @jerridga and the brilliant team behind The Brain Warrior's Way podcast, our friends Dr. Amen @doc_amen and Tana Amen. Click the link in my bio to get your ticket.  

If you or someone you know suffers from #TBI or #PTSD, I highly encourage you to watch this documentary, and share it with your friends. These new breakthroughs could help save someone they love.

node.text:
We’re certainly living through unique times. Over the past year and a half, those of us with school-aged children and young adults in our lives have witnessed this generation navigating and evolving in ways they never could have anticipated. 

As we begin to congratulate students for achieving another milestone year completed along their academic path, let us pause for a moment to acknowledge the amount of focus, sacrifice, and hard work — both physical and emotional — it takes to get here. There’s a tremendous amount of pressure to ACHIEVE, and it can be easy to focus on the awards or recognition you didn’t get, the grade you worked for and wanted but didn’t receive, what you don’t have, or what’s missing. This kind of pressure can take a toll on ANYONE, especially our youth.
 
For #mentalhealthactionday, @marisapolvino @katecohendavis @pamroyblog, my partners on the upcoming feature-length film #manssearchformeaning, will premiere a short film about the dangers of high-pressure schooling — the first in their three-part #meaninginmadness docuseries. My friend @prince_ea hosts the one-hour event, on May 20th, which is open and free to everyone. 

If you have students in your life you support, love, and care about, I encourage you to watch this short film. Sign up at: https://straight-up-impact.com/

I’m excited to share that TOMORROW, Tuesday May 11 at 11 AM PT (2 PM Eastern) I’ll be sitting down with my dear friend Dean Graziosi, along with a lineup of incredible guests, for our first-ever OWN YOUR FUTURE Challenge! We’ll be doing 5 days of live trainings from world-class experts for FREE!  

Now that the world is starting to open up again, we all have the opportunity right now to decide what our life is going to look like in the future – and we have to ask ourselves…  

Do we really want to go “back to normal?” Or do we want to create a whole new reality for ourselves? One where we’re in control of our time, finances, and ultimately the IMPACT we can have in our own communities — and the world. 🌎

Over 830,000 of you joined us this past January for my New World New You Challenge where we focused on creating a mindset for success.  This time @deangraziosi and I are teaming up to show you how to create your own economy in this shifting virtual world. We’ll reveal our top strategies to take back control, get creative again after such a tough year, and create a life of true meaning and impact.  
 
If you’re ready to direct and shape your life — to live it on YOUR terms — then this challenge is for YOU! 
 
Remember, if you talk about it, it’s a dream. If you envision it, it’s possible. But if you schedule it, it’s real. Click the link in my bio to register for FREE now, then block May 11 – 15th in your calendar. Looking forward to connecting with you all TOMORROW — see you there!! 🗓️👨🏻‍💻❤️

node.text:
As a business owner or entrepreneur, it is your opportunity to do more for others than anybody else — in whatever area or industry you’re in.  

It’s about what you GIVE, not what you get.  

And when you’re obsessed with giving more – with meeting and surpassing the needs of your clients, you’ll not only succeed, but you'll make a DIFFERENCE in their lives.  

When you decide to focus on giving instead of getting? You’ll reach more people and touch more lives than ever before – and you’ll GET so much more in return, too. I promise you, when you focus on GIVING and SERVING, you will experience a deeper fulfillment than ever imagined.

The secret to living is giving. ❤️

For all of you business owners, team members, parents, partners, and anyone who provides a service or nurtures a relationship with others, take a moment to consider:  

What business are you REALLY in? How can you FALL IN LOVE with your clients?  

How can we SERVE ONE ANOTHER at the highest level? 

Drop a comment and tell us: What are you really here to GIVE? 🤝❤️

node.text:
Celebrating 22 years with my Sage, my wife, my everything! 😍💘🙏 Valentine's Day is our anniversary and each year, each decade with her is my greatest joy and most treasured gift. I love you, sweetheart!

In our relationships with our beloveds, we are each given the opportunity to wake up to a deeper truth. When we shift our FOCUS to what we are here TO GIVE and TO BECOME for the ones we love — the whole game changes. 

With our family, friends, loved ones, neighbors, teammates — ALL relationships are a place we go to GIVE, not to get.

We give our LIGHT, our PRESENCE, our ATTENTION, and our pure LOVE -- not only on #ValentinesDay but EVERY day!

If you’re not in a relationship right now, this can be a time to clearly define the vision of the love you desire. What would you create and share together? WHO would you be willing TO BECOME to be the best version of yourself for anyone you love? How do you want to show up for your beloveds? And for those of you who are unable to be in physical proximity to your dearest, how could you use creativity and caring to make them feel your love? ❤️ #LOVE

node.text:
Life is a gift and it offers us the privilege, opportunity, and responsibility to give something back by becoming more. 💪💯 

When we use our talents, passions, and the most impactful lessons we’ve learned to lift and serve one another on a deeper, more meaningful level, our souls know that this is truly one of the GREATEST GIFTS we can offer. 🙏❤️

1️⃣ Leave a comment and share ONE personal learning that has played a part in creating massive impact and powerful shifts in your own life.

2️⃣ If a story shared touches you, lifts you up, or inspires you to take action, LIKE IT — let’s show support for each other as we share our experiences. 

We’re all in this together, here to learn from each other, and keep growin’! 📈🤜🤛💥

I AM YOU is a must-watch #film streaming on Amazon and Apple iTunes now! My friend @SoniaNasseryCole is an award-winning Afghan American filmmaker, and the Director and Producer of this profound and deeply moving film. 

There are over 70 million refugees in the world, and half of these are children. It is a life filled with hardship, struggles and uncertainty beyond belief. Sonia’s film, I AM YOU, takes you through the life of three Refugees who leave everything behind and make their way to safety while encountering obstacles that shape their character and their destiny.  

“I Am You is inspired by the story of a refugee, the horrendous conditions before his heroic journey, the heartbreaking indifference confronting him along the way, and the uplifting power and humanity found in hope, truth and justice.” 

Please take a moment to check out I AM YOU on Amazon or iTunes. Once you watch the film, please consider taking a moment to leave a rating of the film and review of your thoughts — this last step will help in Sonia’s mission of spreading knowledge and amplifying voices of those who need to be heard. The more attention we can bring to this cause the more lives we can change together. 🙏🏻❤️ 

🎥 Go to @IAMYOU.film and check out the link in their bio to watch the film.

School is out for summer, and while many children look forward to enjoying the carefree days and warm summer evenings with their families and friends, for over 13M children that means they lose access to school meals and their days are often long and hungry. Many of these children may not know where or when they will get their next meal.  

Our partners at @feedingamerica and their network of food banks are working around the clock to provide over 54 million meals to children and families through summer feeding programs, and they need our help. 

Over the last 7 years, I’ve partnered with Feeding America to help provide 1 billion meals by 2025, and — along with the incredible support of many of you reading this —we're well on our way to meeting our goal! I am so proud to say that we’ve now helped raise 795 MILLION meals for kids, families and individuals facing hunger. 

Our children deserve a summer free from worry. ☀️🧒🏻 ❤️ As families continue to get back on their feet, I invite you to join me in helping make sure children and their families get the food they need. If you feel called to help children and families in need, please click the link in my bio — for every donation made to my 1 Billion Meals Challenge with Feeding America, your donation can be matched, doubling its impact. That means just a $10 donation will provide 200 meals to those in need. 

Awareness is key in our mission to #endhunger, so please consider SHARING this video in your stories to help get the information out to as many people as possible. Together, we can truly make a difference. 🤝 Thank you for your kindness, caring, compassion, and dedication to shine your light and help lift one another in these times. 🙏🏻❤️

* NEW YOUTUBE VIDEO TODAY! * Link in bio * 📺 Sage and I had the privilege of connecting with our beloved friend and dear brother on the path, Sadhguru, and we are absolutely thrilled to share the VIDEO conversation with you all this weekend!  

For those of you who aren’t yet familiar with his tremendous body of work, you’re certainly in for a treat. @sadhguru is a New York Times bestselling author who has been named one of India’s Top 50 most influential people, and is the creator of the Isha Foundation, a non-religious, non-profit organization based at the Isha Yoga Center that’s run by some 9 million volunteers!! 

He is also a motorcycle-riding dad! 🏍 He lives by a unique combination of Eastern wisdom and Western understandings and as always, it was enlightening to discuss with him topics like:

the human mind, 
identity, 
consciousness, 
inner freedom, 
spiritual evolution, 
and his new book Karma: A Yogi’s Guide to Crafting Your Destiny. 

Most of us are familiar with the idea that there is “good Karma” and “bad Karma,” and that somehow our good deeds or wrongdoings stack-up in spiritual debt, ultimately paid through our experiences. But Sadhguru removes the stigma of good and bad and offers a fresh and different understanding of Karma and its common misperceptions.

In this interview, Sadhguru explains that our karma actually has the ability to enhance our lives if only we choose to use our past — and our memories of it — in ways that serve our perception of life, personal evolution, growth, and ultimately, our FREEDOM.  
  
Sadhguru is truly a deeply beautiful soul with such a generous heart, and a lovely sense of humor!

We hope you’re able to take in his profound video for your own inner freedom this weekend. ❤️🙏🙂

Space travel has been totally reimagined! 🚀✨

I’m thrilled to announce that our partners at Space Perspective have successfully completed the test flight launch of Neptune One from the Space Coast Spaceport, adjacent to NASA’s Kennedy Space Center. I am so excited to be a part of this historical moment — together, we are changing the face of space travel. 
 
Instead of rocketing away from the Earth at intense speeds, passengers will ascend on a gentle journey to gaze upon Earth from space — a truly unforgettable experience that astronauts call life-altering. 🌎 And this journey from Earth to Space takes place in just six hours — mind-blowing! 🤯
 
Not only will we be taking people to space, we'll also be conducting ground-breaking research in climate and upper atmospheric science, solar and astrophysics, and astrobiology — and those of you traveling with us as Space Explorers will have an opportunity to participate. 
 
“Space Perspective plans to fly visual, literary, digital, culinary and performing arts to forge collaboration between science, technology, and creativity, illustrating that exploring the world we live in and communicating the human experience is possible in ways that engineering, and technology cannot.” 💙
 
I’m truly honored to partner in this incredible opportunity to inspire, connect, and ultimately remind us that we are all part of a human family sharing this remarkable planet. 🤝🌎
 
#SpacePerspective #SpaceshipNeptune #SpaceFlight #SpaceExploration #AdventureTravel

Do you want to know the FASTEST way to END SUFFERING?  

It’s actually very simple... 

Trade your expectations for appreciation and your WHOLE WORLD will change in an instant. 

I truly believe that we’re living in the greatest time in HISTORY — creativity, innovation, and opportunity exist like never before. We’re blessed to live in an abundant time, where so many of our desires are met instantly — at the touch of a button, the click of your mouse, the swipe of your thumb. Social media links us to people all over the world — we can count the number of “friends,” and we get a dopamine boost with every 👍🏻, ❤️, or 😂.

The crazy thing is, that most of us believe that kind of instant gratification = happiness. But what we’re really experiencing when we’re focused on what we GET in life is the ILLUSION of happiness and fulfillment. We live in a culture of EXPECTATION where we are focused on ourselves and our own needs. And when our desires and expectations aren’t met IMMEDIATELY, we feel lack, loss, frustration, rejection…all states of suffering.  

But the TRUTH is, what makes us TRULY happy in life is NOT what we GET, it’s what we GIVE. After all, the secret to living, is giving! 

When we make the choice to focus on appreciation, growth, contribution, and LOVE, we’re making the conscious decision to live in a beautiful state — no matter what.  🙏🏻❤️

Right now, think of something or someone that you’re grateful for and that you can appreciate in THIS moment. Let’s hear from you in the comments — what do you APPRECIATE today?
